<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 25 at 5:56AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...Areas of Fog Affecting Deep South Texas...
Surface observations indicate that areas of fog have developed
over Zapata, Jim Hogg, Brooks, Starr, and Hidalgo Counties this
morning. Visibilities will range from 1 to 3 miles in the fog,
with some patchy dense fog reducing the visibility to one half of
a mile or less in some areas.
Motorists are urged to reduce speed, use low beam headlights, and
avoid following other vehicles too closely in the areas of denser
fog through the evening and overnight hours.</description>
